## 1. Big picture (one diagram)

```text
  [Developer]
       │
       ├─► Service repo (app code) ──► build image ──► ECR tag
       │
       └─► exotel_configs (Helm chart + values per env)
                 │
                 ▼
       ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
       │  Jenkins (multibranch)               │
       │  • checks out exotel_configs         │
       │  • checks out exotel_deployments     │
       │  • pulls env / branch (master, next) │
       │  • helm template cqa/k8s             │
       │    + values.integration.yaml         │
       │    + values.qa.yaml  (next)          │
       │    + values.mum1.yaml / prod.yaml    │
       │  • writes rendered YAML to           │
       │    exotel_deployments/cqa/{env}/     │
       │  • git commit + push                 │
       └──────────────────────────────────────┘
                 │
                 ▼
       ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
       │  exotel_deployments (Git)            │
       │  cqa/integration/                    │
       │  cqa/qa/          (often from next)  │
       │  cqa/mum1/      (prod-like)        │
       │  cqa/prod/                           │
       └──────────────────────────────────────┘
                 │
                 ▼
       ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
       │  Argo CD                             │
       │  Application → path = cqa/qa (etc.)    │
       │  sync policy → cluster               │
       └──────────────────────────────────────┘
                 │
                 ▼
            [ Kubernetes cluster ]
```

**Interview line:** *“**Desired state** lives in `exotel_configs` as Helm; CI **renders** flat manifests into `exotel_deployments`; **ArgoCD** is the delivery loop from that repo to the cluster.”*

