## 4. What “Helm generation” does (no magic)

On the agent (or Jenkins worker):

```bash
cd exotel_configs/cqa/k8s
helm template cqa . \
  -f values/values.qa.yaml \
  --set image.tag="${IMAGE_TAG}" \
  > /tmp/rendered.yaml
```

Then CI **splits** or **writes** into `exotel_deployments/cqa/qa/` (layout your org defines — sometimes one `rendered.yaml`, sometimes split resources).

Local **compare** script in **this workspace**: `Implementation/CQA/scripts/pull-render-and-compare.sh` — same **helm template** idea for integration, qa, mum1, prod. Override paths:

`EXOTEL_CONFIGS=/path/to/exotel_configs EXOTEL_DEPLOYMENTS=/path/to/exotel_deployments ./pull-render-and-compare.sh`

